def: Situated at, or near, the apex; apical.
To make a gash, or long, deep incision in; -- applied chieflyto incisions in flesh.Grievously gashed or gored to death. Hayward.
Troubled; dark; gloomy. [Obs.] "With full trouble cheer."Chaucer.
1. Preserving; rescuing.He is the saving strength of his anointed. Ps. xxviii. 8.
A woman who violates her religious engagements. James iv. 4.
To bury; also, to engrave. [Obs.] Gower.
The state of being recusant; nonconformity. Coke.
Of or pertaining to the period immediately following thePliocene; Pleistocene. Also used as a noun. See Quaternary.

An opposition or contrast of words or sentiments occurring inthe same sentence; as, "The prodigal robs his heir; the miser robshimself." "He had covertly shot at Cromwell; he how openly aimed atthe Queen."
The people who lived in the Middle Ages. Ruskin.
Belonging to, or resembling, a suborder of composite plants ofwhich the chicory (Cichorium) is the type.
